{
  "name": "prefrontal_circuit",
  "description": "Minimal dorsolateral prefrontal cortex — sustained goal maintenance + rule learning. Real PFC: pyramidal cells maintain persistent activity (working memory for goals), interneurons enforce one-rule-at-a-time (mutual exclusion), dopamine modulates which rule is active. Our version: 2 RS goal cells maintain sustained activity via self-excitation (like working_memory but with PLASTIC inputs for rule learning). 2 CH bistable cells provide persistent on/off state (the 'goal register'). 1 FS provides local lateral inhibition (one goal at a time). 1 LTS provides sustained suppression when goal changes (clear old goal). 2 RS output cells: one for current goal, one for goal-switch signal. STDP on input->goal: learns which inputs predict which goals from experience. The key PFC feature: goals PERSIST after stimulus ends (unlike sensory responses). Implements: sustained attention, rule-based behavior, goal maintenance, set shifting.",
